From: my-other-github-account
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] dflash: reset n_past + clear drafter KV on begin()

PR #22105's common_speculative_state_dflash::begin() was a no-op,
relying on `dflash_n_past = 0` only at construction time. But the
state object lives for the entire server-slot lifetime — so on the
SECOND request handled by the same slot, `dflash_n_past` still
points at the end of the first request's accumulated context.

When the second request's prompt is shorter than the previous
prompt+output (e.g. a fresh user turn after a long completion),
the draft step computes:

    n_new = n - dflash_n_past   <= 0

and trips:

    common/speculative.cpp:781:
    GGML_ASSERT(n_new >= 1 && "must have at least 1 new token") failed

aborting the server. Symptom in production: server happily handles the
first /v1/chat/completions call, then aborts mid-flight on the second.

Fix: in begin(), reset dflash_n_past, clear accumulated_ctx, and
clear the KV memory for both encoder and decoder drafter contexts.
This matches the cross-request-reset pattern used by the EAGLE3-with-
checkpoint path higher up in the same file (line 246-).

---
 common/speculative.cpp | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/common/speculative.cpp b/common/speculative.cpp
--- a/common/speculative.cpp
+++ b/common/speculative.cpp
@@ -763,6 +763,15 @@ struct common_speculative_state_dflash : public common_speculative_state {
 
     void begin(const llama_tokens & prompt) override {
         GGML_UNUSED(prompt);
+        // Reset cross-request state. Without this, dflash_n_past from a prior
+        // request causes n_new = n - dflash_n_past <= 0 on a new shorter
+        // prompt and trips the GGML_ASSERT(n_new >= 1) below.
+        dflash_n_past = 0;
+        accumulated_ctx.clear();
+        llama_memory_t mem_enc = llama_get_memory(ctx_dft_enc);
+        if (mem_enc) llama_memory_clear(mem_enc, false);
+        llama_memory_t mem_dec = llama_get_memory(ctx_dft_dec);
+        if (mem_dec) llama_memory_clear(mem_dec, false);
     }
 
     void draft(
